# VR Hotspots — development map

## Run locally

```bash
npm install
npm run dev:feature   # API :3001, Vite editor :5174
npm start             # production-style single server (:3000)
```

Copy `.env.example` → `.env`. Never commit `.env`. Deploy docs: `RENDER_DEPLOY.md`.

## Architecture (critical)

Most logic lives in **`script.js`** (~15k lines). There are **two runtimes**:

| Change affects… | Edit here |
|-----------------|-----------|
| Editor sidebar, dialogs, placement | `HotspotEditor` class (~line 131) |
| Exported / standalone projects | `generateCompleteJS()` (~line 9284) |
| Exported styling | `generateCSS()` (~line 9039) |
| Editor hotspot behavior | `editor-spot` component (~line 14820) |
| Exported hotspot behavior | `hotspot` inside `generateCompleteJS` (~line 9356) |

**Rule:** UI-only changes stay in `HotspotEditor` / `index.html`. Anything students see in exported ZIPs must also be updated inside `generateCompleteJS()` (code inside its template literal is what gets shipped).

## Other key files

- **`index.html`** — editor layout, panel order, CSS for admin UI
- **`simple-server.js`** — Express app, static files, submission upload
- **`routes/common-assets-routes.js`** + **`lib/common-assets.js`** — shared B2 asset library
- **`services/b2-service.js`** — Backblaze upload/download
- **`admin-dashboard.html`**, **`admin-common-assets.html`** — admin UIs

## Persistence & export

- Scene/hotspot data: `saveScenesData()`, localStorage, IndexedDB (search `.saveToIDB`, `rehydrate`)
- Student ZIP export: `saveAsCompleteProject()` / `normalizeScenePathsForExport()` — supports bundle vs URL modes
- Common asset URLs must work in exported projects (direct B2 URLs or bundled relative paths)

## Conventions

- Match existing patterns; avoid large refactors of `script.js` unless requested
- Test both **editor** and **re-exported project** after hotspot or A-Frame behavior changes
- A-Frame is vendored locally (`node_modules/aframe`) — no CDN in exports
